where Cov(Xi, Xj; w) represents the covariance of Xi and Xj after being reweighted by PÀúw. DWR is well Ô¨Åtted for the case where the data generation process is dominated by a
linear function, since it focuses on linear decorrelation only.

SRDO (Shen et al. 2020b) conducts sample reweighting

by density ratio estimation. It simulates the target distri-

bution PÀú by means of random resampling on each covari-

ate so that PÀú(X1, X2, . . . , Xp) =

